        <object label="Product Modelling Ontology" Description="This ontology structures the lifecycle of a product, detailing components, features, and configurations from design to manufacturing. It captures relationships among different product elements, focusing on specifications, material properties, and functional requirements." Id="302" References="" placeholders="1" Role="Unlike abstract design ontologies, this is practical and component-focused, emphasizing usability in engineering and manufacturing for real-world production." id="7iJxjdkOMapWwhl0Z6aH-1801">
